    {
      "kind": "parameters",
      "parameters": [
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "A rendering context  attached to the window that’s the target of the texture operation.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "context"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "A constant that specifies an OpenGL target texture. You can supply any of the texture targets defined by the OpenGL specification, including:",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            },
            {
              "items": [
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "inlineContent": [
                        {
                          "code": "GL_TEXTURE_2D",
                          "type": "codeVoice"
                        },
                        {
                          "text": ", a texture whose dimensions are a power of two.",
                          "type": "text"
                        }
                      ],
                      "type": "paragraph"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "inlineContent": [
                        {
                          "code": "GL_TEXTURE_RECTANGLE_EXT",
                          "type": "codeVoice"
                        },
                        {
                          "text": ", a texture whose dimensions are not a power of two.",
                          "type": "text"
                        }
                      ],
                      "type": "paragraph"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "inlineContent": [
                        {
                          "code": "GL_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP",
                          "type": "codeVoice"
                        },
                        {
                          "text": ", a mapped cube texture.",
                          "type": "text"
                        }
                      ],
                      "type": "paragraph"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ],
              "type": "unorderedList"
            }
          ],
          "name": "target"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "A constant that specifies the internal color format of the texture— either ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "code": "GL_RGB",
                  "type": "codeVoice"
                },
                {
                  "text": " or ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "code": "GL_RGBA",
                  "type": "codeVoice"
                },
                {
                  "text": ".",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "internalformat"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "A rendering context that’s attached to the window that’s the source of the texture data.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "surfacecontext"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "Discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "aglSurfaceTexture",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " function behaves similar to the function ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "glTexImage2D",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ". The texture target and internal format must be supported by the renderer of the target rendering context, and the geometry of the source drawable object must be compatible with the texture target. For example, if the texture target is ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "GL_TEXTURE_2D",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ", the window must conform to power-of-two dimensions.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Before calling this function you must use OpenGL calls to set up the OpenGL texture referred to by the target parameter. That is, enable texturing, generate a texture name, bind it to a texture target, and so forth. For more information, see ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "http://www.opengl.org/documentation/red_book/",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The target and source windows must use the same renderer (virtual screen) or the function fails, most typically by not texturing the target rendering context.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "An error condition occurs if the surface rendering context is not attached to a windowed drawable object; the drawable object cannot be an offscreen area or pixel buffer. It’s also possible to get standard OpenGL errors similar to the errors that can occur for the function ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "glTexImage2D",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ". Use the function ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "glError",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " to query OpenGL errors.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": " ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "Although the function ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "code": "aglSurfaceTexture",
                  "type": "codeVoice"
                },
                {
                  "text": " provides a flexible way to render to an offscreen texture and then use it as a source, you should consider using pixel buffer objects or OpenGL framebuffer objects instead. For details on using a hidden window as a texture source, see ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "identifier": "https://developer.apple.com/library/archive/documentation/GraphicsImaging/Conceptual/OpenGL-MacProgGuide/opengl_intro/opengl_intro.html#//apple_ref/doc/uid/TP40001987",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "type": "reference"
                },
                {
                  "text": ". This document also describes how to use pixel buffer objects and framebuffer objects as texture sources.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Note",
          "style": "note",
          "type": "aside"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
